John Jay Dining Hall is Columbia's largest and, for me, most homely dining hall. The dining hall food here is also the most varied. On Mondays, watch out if you like meat. John Jay serves no main meat entrees for Green Monday every week. There are meat options available, but the lines for these options do get long on Mondays.

Came here on a romantic evening for two and it was, quite frankly, stunning. The ambience was superb; flowers on the table, and a pleasant hum from other happy guests. Food took my breath away. Admittedly, this was because at one point I was choking on my broccoli, it was big. Fortunately the staff get an A+ for heimlich manouvre - thank you, Fran. You saved my life. I love you. And I love the USA.
